# Trivy/tfsec ignores for terraform-aws-eks-cluster. Each entry uses an AVD-
# prefixed ID (required when a resource is scanned through a module call) and
# carries a justification. Keep this list tight — prefer fixing at the source.

# AVD-AWS-0017 — "CloudWatch log group is not encrypted with a customer-managed key".
#
# Applies to aws_cloudwatch_log_group.default (the EKS control-plane log group
# in main.tf). Control-plane logs are encrypted at rest with an AWS-managed key
# by default; a customer-managed key is bring-your-own via
# `cloudwatch_log_group_kms_key_id`. We don't force a module-created CMK here
# because the CloudWatch Logs service must be granted usage on that key via its
# key policy, which belongs with the caller's KMS module (terraform-aws-kms),
# not inlined per-cluster. examples/complete demonstrates supplying a key.
AVD-AWS-0017
